data.name: label17.Text
data.value: Taskbar displays your opened applications and allows you to open Start menu. It also displays system notifications. While usually located at the bottom of the screen, the taskbar can be moved to other sides of the screen.

data.name: label9.Text
data.value: Select one of the colours below or use advanced colour options to personalize your window colour. Due to certain API limits, colour changes will not apply to taskbar, Start menu and UWP applications in this version.

data.name: label14.Text
data.value: Screen savers are used to display some moving objects on the screen while the user is away for a long time. This can protect the older displays from a phospor burn-in. Another feature of screen savers is to offer basic security, e.g. requiring a password before user can use the computer again.
